result.adr_address: 23 Hak Po St, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 23 Hak Po St, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.name: Ramen Kureha 拉麵來

reviews.text:
I would have 5 stars for the favour, the staff friendliness and the decor, but the price is on the higher side, but you get what you paid for. 

I had the pork bone black garlic ramen lunch combo and the soup is hardy and flavorful. At first taste, it seems underseasoned but you realize that you can really taste that pork bone meatiness/sweetness without too much that kombu/dashi msg favour. The charsiu is favour, chucky and tender.

Because of price and food took too long to prepare. I gave it 4.5 stars.

a great Japanese ramen shop like Ippudo. The interior decoration is like Japan in 1960. Price is on the high side but quality is great. Difficult for foreigners to place order though because you place your order on a reusable plastic card with no English translation.
Good service. Ramen is okay. Price is reasonable
Yummy ramen shop,a bit on the pricey side but with the extra dollar for the consistently delicious food. Good option for a quick bite for those around MK.
Best ramen in kowloon.

result.adr_address: 香港旺角黑布街23號
result.name: Ramen Kureha 拉麵來

reviews.text: 湯底濃味冇乜味精。麵可以。配料夠多。叉燒兩大塊好普通肉唔係咁嫩。追加溏心蛋略凍。連溏心蛋盛惠$115太過進取。
香港最好吃的拉麵店，湯底濃郁，麵條彈性十足，店內裝潢很有日本風味，十分推薦！
裝潢很有特色，食物質素也好。
有大坑店水準可以一試
